ional\nWholesale Dry Goods Association, j\nat its convention this week, frowned\nupon advancing prices at this time- j\nIt was brought out that the -increase*\nbeing made now may have;\ntwo undesirable effects?dne. to]\ncheck the reaiy fl? w of merchandise\nin its customary channels, and the;\nother, to bring about a renewal of\nthe consumer'a-strike. Retailers. It\nwas explained further/might suddenly\nease liquidation If the upward\nmovement gets far. thus leading\nt-. a repetUion of the condltlonr\nbefore the Readjustment period. Th\"\nsentiment was distinctly agamat all\nadvances, except tiros ta.idc absolutely\nnecessary. This view was\nlak<*n not only hj the wholesalers,\nbut by textile representatives present.\"\nUNERS REVEL\nCANDY KISSES\nDN TAUT CABLE\nWilliam McNelr. A H Ijvmhi. Chart**\nli. Botfr, William C. Jobnaon. Charie* B\nl^ddaiM*. J. C. liannaii B K U intun.\nC. .4. kfigoa. Chaa. A. Kr?m. F. P. ffi\nwkk. Ham J. Steinberger. MarahsU Klug\nI'hillp J. Udiwarti. Clarence E. F\nII. KpfBctr Dr Insan. B. i. Dr\nJ Simpson. Jr.. Court F Wood. Hear? B\nDari*. 8 II. Malta. G. C. Bradford. J C\nDr. Burch, J. W Ilarhngtoa.\nW. Church. The*. P. Sptake O. W Shu\nmute. Mr. lloff. Fraak J Hogan. Wm H.\nIlonovaa. A. A Bra Ml I K. F. Harper. W\nK. loaiR. II K Wijlard J. kl Boteler.\nJ. V riUfrn^. J?weph U. Teitti. W H.\nWarner. Harmon K Warner. (TarMK* W.\nW?n?r. E. J. Vana. (ivoifr P. Wtlcn.\nCbarlc* Jacobaen. A. F Jon?, Hohert L.\nStunt. N. Mountfard. Harry Gordon. B\nMcNeil. J Paul Smith, John L. Fugitt.\nW W Keek. Char la* P Ra re n bur* J\nI-co Knlb. J C Petty, Dunnd 8 Piatt.\nR L. MrKeerer. W. W. Brut. K J. Bojd.\nSidney Roche, l>r. W 8. Rlchardaon. CharW\nKeller. Theodore P. Noyea. W (V Murph>.\n?*ee. M Mye?, Marshall MiKihben. Tbw\nB. AM|ai?h. I'tTMnn C. Kin*. I>r. H. C.\nOberholaer. F P. Avalear. Arthur Steinberg,\nleather W. lankinv H. ti. Lehman. Claude\nUober?on. F P. WtlroJ, W V Ward. J.\nJ Mattery. E T. tinodnaa. W Goodman.\nK L. Goodman. (ieorff M. Hun